name: r-rastervis
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.51.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rastervis
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rasterVis_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rasterVis/rasterVis_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c116f979ed891ec55f3e1e7b9a92436b5ec9430c1170439a501ecb7e2a33ef4d

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/


requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-hexbin
    - r-lattice >=0.20_41
    - r-latticeextra
    - r-raster >=2.0_12
    - r-sp >=1.0_6
    - r-terra
    - r-viridislite
    - r-zoo
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-hexbin
    - r-lattice >=0.20_41
    - r-latticeextra
    - r-raster >=2.0_12
    - r-sp >=1.0_6
    - r-terra
    - r-viridislite
    - r-zoo

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rasterVis')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rasterVis')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://oscarperpinan.github.io/rastervis
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Methods for enhanced visualization and interaction with raster data. It implements visualization methods for quantitative data and categorical data, both for univariate and multivariate rasters. It also provides methods to display spatiotemporal rasters, and vector fields. See the website for examples.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ocefpaf
